

'''Paulus Kal''' was a [[15th century]] [[Germany|German]] [[fencing]] master. In [[1460]], he wrote a [[Fechtbuch|combat manual]] describing the art of fencing (Cgm 1507, 95 folia).

==Literature==
*Christian Henry Tobler, ''In Service of the Duke: The 15th Century Fighting Treatise of Paulus Kal'', Chivalry Bookshelf (2006) [http://chivalrybookshelf.com/titles/Kal/Kal.htm]

